common.Reports

Class OrderReport

  • java.lang.Object
    • common.Reports.OrderReport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class OrderReport
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The OrderReport class is a data structure used to store information about the orders made from a specific vending machine. It contains information such as the machine ID, location, number of orders made, and the month and year of the orders. This class implements the Serializable interface, which allows it to be written to a file or sent over a network.
